CEUR-WS.org - CEUR Workshop Proceedings (free, open-access publishing, computer science/information systems) CEUR Workshop Proceedings (CEUR-WS.org) is a free , diamond open-access publication service
               at Sun SITE Central Europe operated under the umbrella of RWTH Aachen University and listed
               in the Bielefeld ISSN-GOLD-OA dataset ,
               the JUFO database ,
               and the DIAMAS registry of diamond
                  open-access publishers .
               CEUR-WS.org is a recognized ISSN publication series, ISSN 1613-0073 ( json ).
               CEUR-WS.org is hosted at http://SunSITE.Informatik.RWTH-Aachen.DE/Publications/CEUR-WS/.
               This service is provided by
               the CEUR-WS.org Team .
               See end of the page for contact details and Impressum . CEUR-WS.org Team | FAQ | How to submit ( happy path ) | GenAI Policy | AIxIA Series | IAOA Series | Blog | Long-term archive | CEUR Workshop Proceedings (CEUR-WS.org) Free Open-Access Proceedings for Computer Science Workshops Unless stated explicitely and in conformance to the legal Disclaimer of Sun
         SITE
         Central Europe (CEUR) and the legal Disclaimer of
         Technical University of Aachen (RWTH), the copyright
         for the workshop proceedings as a compilation,
         i.e. CEUR-WS.org/Vol-1, CEUR-WS.org/Vol-2 etc., is with the
         respective proceedings editors.
         The copyright for the individual items (subsuming any type of computer-represented files
         containing articles, software demos, videos, etc.) within a proceedings volume is owned by their respective
         authors/owners. The open-access license for a volume is specified in the index file of the respective volume.
         This license applies by default to all components in the volume. Re-publication of a CEUR Workshop Proceedings volume or of an individual item inside a proceedings
         volume
         requires permission by the copyright owners, i.e. either the respective proceedings editors, or
         the authors of the respective item in that volume, or both.
         Mirroring of the CEUR-WS.org web site, or parts of
         it, is prohibited. The label 'CEUR Workshop Proceedings' and
         the CEUR-WS logo are owned
         by the members of the CEUR-WS Team, represented by its editor-in-chief.
         CEUR-WS.org provides its services free of charge to the academic community.
         CEUR-WS.org is not run by an organization but by volunteers from
         different universities, who realize the service in their spare time. Important changes are reported in our timeline .
         We are grateful for donations of scripts that ease our tasks, for example scripts
         that detect errors in index files. Proceedings editors: Publishing with CEUR-WS: The Happy Path covers the recommended submission steps for a smooth submission process and should suffice in most cases. For
      additional details about CEUR-WS submission handling,
      please refer to the instructions on how to submit page. 2022-04-05: Due to the ongoing war in Ukraine, CEUR-WS suspends until further notice submissions from Russian and
      Belarussian institutions. 2025-01-01: CEUR-WS adopts a new policy about using Generative AI in papers. This policy mandates that authors:
      i) declare the use of GenAI tools in the paper, ii) review and edit any AI-generated content, and iii) not list AI
      tools as authors. Read more . 2025-06-13: We make the bash scripts check-pdf-errors and check-index-errors available to
      workshop organizers to check compliance of paper PDFs and the index.html file with our style. 2025-09-17: GI eV will become the new sponsor and hoster of
      CEUR-WS.org. 2025-09-18: Our template Vol-XXX now explains how to add ORCIDs to the volume editors and
      to authors.
      This feature is optional. Workshop organizers can decide not to use it. 2025-09-23: Gianluca Amato has written a Python script to create the page numbers for the index.html file from the
      PDF files. Have look at ceur-add-pagenum . Nutt Submitted by: Manfred Jeusfeld Published on CEUR-WS: 7-Apr-1995 ONLINE: https://ceur-ws.org/Vol-1/ URN: urn:nbn:de:0074-1-5 ARCHIVE: http://sunsite.informatik.rwth-aachen.de/ftp/pub/publications/CEUR-WS/Vol-1.zip Miscellaneous Workshop organizers can look here for information on how to submit
         electronic workshop proceedings to CEUR. The procedure takes
         few minutes. The slides of our prtesentation at the 2019 Open Access Tage in Hannover, 2019-10-02 are available here . Some statistics about CEUR-WS.org.
         In January 2011, CEUR-WS.org published about 10.500 papers
         distributed over roughly 680 volumes.
         There were a few thousand real paper downloads
         (downloads by search engines and from the proceedings FTP archive not counted) per
         day from CEUR-WS.org.
         In Nov 2017, CEUR-WS.org had published about 35.000 papers
         distributed over roughly 1970 volumes.
         The number of real paper downloads reaches now several ten thousands per day.
         Between
         1995 and 2020, CEUR-WS.org was offline for less than 10 days in total.
         The offline times were
         mostly due to network re-configurations at RWTH Aachen. Since its start in 1995,
         the number of volumes published per year has shown solid growth . As a supplement to the ONLINE access, there is an ARCHIVE link pointing to a compressed version
         of the publication, i.e. all papers plus the index file,
         that can be downloaded as a single 'zip' archive file.
         For questions about indexing of CEUR-WS proceedings volumes in publication databases such as DBLP , please see our FAQ . Anbieterkennzeichnung/Impressum nach Paragraph 6 TDG: CEUR-WS Team, Redaktion Sun SITE, Informatik V,
